        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 11:02PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 1102 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Metropolis to Brookport to near Lone Oak.
Movement was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hamletsburg, Burna, Ledbetter, Reidland, Smithland, Kuttawa, Calvert
City, Paducah, Salem, Grand Rivers, Dycusburg, Demumbers Bay
Campground, Brookport, Eddyville, and Land Between The Lakes Area.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 24 in Kentucky between Mile Markers 7 and 43.
Interstate 24 in Illinois between Mile Markers 30 and 36.
Interstate 69 in Kentucky between Mile Markers 49 and 70.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for southern
Illinois...and western Kentucky.</instruction>
